summary: Los Angeles Dodgers star Mookie Betts sustained a broken left hand after being hit by a 98 mph fastball during a game against the Kansas City Royals. Betts was placed on the injured list and is expected to miss several weeks, though he will not require surgery. The injury is a significant blow to the Dodgers, who are currently in contention for the National League West title. Betts is a five-time Gold Glove winner and a four-time Silver Slugger, and is considered one of the best all-around players in Major League Baseball.

His untimely demise has left the culinary community, friends, and family deeply saddened. summary: Dad jokes, a hallmark of fatherhood, evoke laughter and ignite conversations. From chuckled-out absurdities in "250 Dad Jokes That You Can't Help but Laugh At" to a humorous Father's Day reflection by Pastor Bo, the tradition of dad jokes is celebrated. "An homage to the dad joke" explores its cultural significance, while "40 fun, corny and silly 'dad jokes'" provides ready-to-share gems for the upcoming holiday. Mo Welch's "Dad Jokes" contextualizes humor in real-time, while research reveals the surprising psychology behind their appeal in "Why dad jokes crack us up." Interestingly, the Federal Government is even funding dad jokes, and Panera is offering gift cards for "Souper" qualified dad joke-tellers. Monty's Dad Jokes and A.J. Jacobs' incorporation of dad jokes into his book showcase their enduring presence in various contexts.
